added.title: Lucky Stars
added.description: Raven explains astrology to the Titans and tells their horoscopes, but Cyborg does not believe.

added.title: Various Modes of Transportation
added.description: With the other Titans away, Cyborg is forced to take a road trip with Robin.

added.title: Cool Uncles
added.description: The Titans take a trip to Wackadoodles, but Trigon makes Raven babysit her little brothers.

added.title: The Sorcerer
added.description: Gumball refuses to accept he is the only kid at school that doesn't have special powers. He convinces Mrs. Jotunheim, Hector's mom, to take him on as his apprentice but she soon learns leaving Gumball unsupervised around magic is a big mistake.

added.title: The Menu
added.description: The prize jewel on the Secret Joyful Burger menu is a mysterious burger, but to order it you need to know its name. When Larry refuses to tell them what it's called, they go to super-sized lengths to discover it.

added.title: The Uncle
added.description: Gumball and Darwin are desperate to meet Ocho's famous uncle.

added.title: The Weirdo
added.description: When they see the school bullies making fun of Sussie, Gumball and Darwin decide to try and help her act less weird. They carefully observe her behavior and decide that the only thing they have to change is absolutely everything.

added.title: The Heist
added.description: Richard discovers going into a bank whilst wearing a motorcycle helmet can land you in a lot of trouble.

added.title: The Kid From 3030
added.description: The kids meet a mysterious kid from the future and try to help him complete his mission.

added.title: Power Punchers
added.description: Fed up with losing in video games to his Dad, Craig seeks training in the Creek.

added.title: Creek Cart Racers
added.description: A high-speed race with a high-stakes prize may be too much for Craig and his friends.

added.title: Secret Book Club
added.description: Kelsey starts a super secret book club to introduce Craig and JP to the joys of reading.

added.title: Jextra Perrestrial
added.description: JP believes he may be from another planet, so Craig tries to help him make contact.

added.title: Happy Bouncy Fun Town
added.description: The Bears land in the cheeriest place of all time, but Ice Bear starts to feel out of place.

added.title: Back to Our Regular Time Period
added.description: The Bears find themselves trapped in the wrong time period.

added.title: Bath on the Nile
added.description: The Bears find themselves in an ancient Egyptian spa, but Grizz refuses to take a bath.

added.title: Temple Bears
added.description: The Bears search for a house key in a puzzle-filled temple.

added.title: Lighthouse
added.description: The Bears find a lighthouse powered by a luminous creature.

added.title: Stay Goth, Poodle Girl, Stay Goth
added.description: Gwen accidentally brings a pink stuffed pony she loves to daycare and spends the day denying it's hers.

added.title: Gum and Gummer
added.description: Beth gets her gum stuck in Leshawna's hair and has to get it out - without Leshawna finding out it's there.

added.title: Invasion of the Booger Snatchers
added.description: Harold believes that the picture day photographer is somehow turning the kids into well behaved zombies.

added.title: Wristy Business
added.description: Beth and Leshawna try to one-up each other with fake injuries as they compete for the attention and sympathy of the other kids at daycare.

added.title: Melter Skelter
added.description: When Chef tells Beth he won't buy the new super amazing toy she wants because they already have plenty to play with, she goes on a mission to get rid of their toys.

added.title: Lambporcini
added.description: Apple and Onion are very happy with their sweet new matching designer outfits they bought from known scam-artist Street Dog. That's until Chicken Nugget mistakes them for something they are not.

added.title: Jerk Chicken
added.description: In pursuit of the American Dream, Apple and Onion start their own business. However, a rather troublesome customer stands in their way.

added.title: Open House Cookies
added.description: Jerk Chicken is selling his house and Apple and Onion have been showing a lot of interest which definitely has nothing to do with the delicious cookies out on offer.

added.title: World Cup
added.description: It's time to relax in the expensive massage chairs that Apple & Onion have rented for the month. It's also time for the Football (soccer) World Cup and Falafel's team, Egypt are in the tournament..

added.title: Win It or Bin It
added.description: Apple and Onion are about to take ownership of a brand new luxury penthouse apartment and be rid of their roof shack for ever! All they need is a good reference from a previous landlord… Falafel.

added.title: Beach Heads
added.description: After traveling to Tampa Beach, Florida, Team Tennyson hopes to get some much-needed rest & relaxation, but the tempests without a temper, the Weatherheads, have other plans that Ben must thwart: to build a new beach base!

added.title: Charm School's Out
added.description: During a family cookout at a forest campsite, Charmcaster users her magic to switch places with Gwen, but when Ben catches "Charmcaster" sneaking about, he attacks, unaware it's actually his cursed cousin!

added.title: Cyber Slammers
added.description: At Biggie Box Japan, Ben waits in an epic line for the release of the latest Sumo Slammers video game, Cyber Slammers, but Ben must save the store not from game-hungry customers, but from Steam Smythe, who wants to retro-fit a massive mech with steam punk powers!

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: When Ben and family go to London to visit the legendary Big Ben, the Bugg Brothers are there to greet them, with yet another outrageously over the top plan of course: to shrink the Big Ben bell in order to steal it!

added.title: LaGrange Muraille
added.description: While visiting China, Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max take a trek to the Great Wall, but their adventure is nearly ruined by daredevils LaGrange and Vin Ethanol trying to jump the international monument, and Ben must hop into the Rustbuggy to chase away the fast and furious foes.

added.title: The Galactic Enforcers
added.description: Ben joins a trio of intergalactic alien heroes tracking down the bounty hunter Six Six. But this bunch of heroes is not all it's cracked up to be.

added.title: Camp Fear
added.description: When a race of alien mushrooms takes over a summer camp, Ben discovers a whole new alien to battle the menace.

added.title: Ultimate Weapon
added.description: When Max finds out that part of an alien weapon has been unearthed in Texas, he becomes obsessed with finding it. In doing so, he leads Ben and Gwen on a wild adventure.

added.title: Tough Luck
added.description: Gwen's Lucky Girl powers return when she buys a magical stone at a magic convention in Las Vegas. However, Hex is after the same stone, and after his niece breaks him out of prison, the two set off to retrieve the stone.

added.title: They Lurk Below
added.description: Max's old friend has built the world's only underwater resort, and Ben, Gwen and Max are invited for a sneak peak. But it turns out in order to power the resort, Max's friend took an energy orb from a race of underwater aliens. Now, the aliens want their energy orb back and destroy the resort in order to get it.

added.title: Clyde Five
added.description: Ben's country cousin wants to be a hero, too.

added.title: Rook Tales
added.description: Rook's former teacher will preserve Revonnahgander traditions at any cost.

added.title: Charm School
added.description: At Gwen's college, Ben suspects a new teacher and new student are old enemies.

added.title: The Ballad of Mr. Baumann
added.description: The grouchy storekeeper has a big secret, and she's not of this Earth.

added.title: Fight at the Museum
added.description: Alien artifacts in Bellwood attract enemies from the future and friends from the past.

added.title: Ocean Gem
added.description: The Ocean disappears on the first day of summer and Beach City is in a panic.

added.title: House Guest
added.description: After injuring his leg, Greg comes to live with Steven and unintentionally interferes with Steven's powers.

added.title: Space Race
added.description: Steven attempts to build a spaceship to let Pearl revisit the wonders of the cosmos.

added.title: Secret Team
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Pearl accidentally pop a bubbled gem and form Secret Team to secretly retrieve the missing shards.

added.title: Island Adventure
added.description: Steven takes Lars and Sadie on a vacation to a magical beach to mend their friendship.

added.title: Vault of Bones
added.description: Finn's worried Flame Princess still has evil tendencies in her and wants to shift her alignment to good.

added.title: Mystery Dungeon
added.description: Ice King, NEPTR, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab are trapped inside a mysterious dungeon and must work together to free themselves.

added.title: All Your Fault
added.description: Princess Bubblegum sends Finn and Jake to investigate a message of distress from the Earls of Lemongrab.

added.title: Little Dude
added.description: While Finn and Jake go swimming, Finn's hat magically comes to life!

added.title: Skips in the Saddle
added.description: Skips wants to start dating again.

added.title: Thomas Fights Back
added.description: Thomas Wants to get the park founder's statue back.

added.title: Bachelor Party! Zingo!
added.description: Skips must plan the perfect bachelor party for his cousin, Quips.

added.title: Tent Trouble
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby must replace CJ's expensive tent before she realizes they destroyed it.

added.title: Real Date
added.description: Mordecai and CJ want to go on a romantic date.

added.title: Career Day
added.description: After an excessive spending spree, the Golden Goose tells the gang it won't give them any more golden eggs until they learn the value of money. Following Rick's advice to save money, the gang open a cookie shop to make money on their own and save it in a huge vault.

added.title: Asteroid Blues
added.description: An asteroid is headed right for the kingdom, so Dr Fox leads the gang on a mission to save the kingdom by flying a rocket to the asteroid's surface and blowing it to bits with a huge bomb. But when they get there the gang finds the lonely asteroid is actually a super nice guy and don't want to blow him up.

added.title: The Big Trip
added.description: It's time for the gang's yearly vacation, but Hawk refuses to go, claiming the gang's vacations are never fun for him because the others are terrible at vacationing. Hawk only agrees to go if the gang pass his super-intense vacation training course.

added.title: Late Night Talky Time
added.description: The moon is bored of taking the nightshift, since everyone's always asleep. So Unikitty leads the gang in putting on an over-the-top late night talk show to keep the moon occupied.

added.title: Welcome to the Unikingdom
added.description: After Unikitty finds out that tourism is down in the Unikingdom, she recruits the gang to make a tourism video to inspire people to visit the kingdom. But after calamities come one after another, Unikitty begins to think the video is going to turn out to be a disaster. However the friends save the day with some creativity and manage to get a single tourist to visit. Mission accomplished!

added.title: Criss Cross Crisis
added.description: Another one of the Professor's plans goes awry when he tries to switch apples for oranges causing the entire town to switch from one body to another. The girls must remedy the situation.

added.title: Town and Out/Child Fearing
added.description: Town and Out: When the Professor gets a new job, the girls have to move away from Townsville. They try to make the best of it but it's just not the same. In fact, it's downright awful./Child Fearing: When the Mayor needs someone to babysit the girls for him, Mojo is unwittingly drafted. Little does Mojo know, taking care of three little girls can be a big hassle.

added.title: Bubblevision/Bought and Scold
added.description: Bubblevision: Bubbles' fighting has been really terribly lately and the Professor discovers she needs glasses. Bubbles is humiliated by these huge, horrible things and never wants to see or be seen again./Bough and Scold: When Princess buys Townsville, she makes crime legal. Now, the girls have nothing to do and the town is in shambles.

added.title: In the Garden of Good and Eddie
added.description: When the girls try a quick-fix on their neglected veggie garden, they are left with a giant, mooching tomato worm they must care for.

added.title: Road Trippin'
added.description: Realizing her and the Professor don't have much in common, Bubbles schedules a road trip with just the two of them.

added.title: The Big Sleep
added.description: When the Professor's latest invention wreaks havoc in the house, it's up to the Powerpuff Girls to stop it before it escapes.

added.title: The Secret Life of Blossom Powerpuff
added.description: When Blossom can't join her favorite school club, she imagines what her life would be like if she joined other clubs.

added.title: Halt and Catch Silico
added.description: When a series of negative articles about the Powerpuff Girls are posted on the Internet, the girls track them back to Silico.

added.title: Dog Hotel
added.description: With no place to stay while their cave gets fumigated, the Bears book a night at a hotel for dogs.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Rough Riders Elementary
added.description: When a corporate sponsorship of Clarence's school turns into an ominous corporate takeover, Clarence must stand up to the the man, no matter how tasty the chicken may be.

added.title: Nothing Ventured
added.description: Clarence and Sumo look to throw together some quick cash so they can invest in Chad and Sumo's dad's new business venture, a boutique sculpture shop.

added.title: Bedside Manners
added.description: After a nasty spill lands Belson in a full body cast, Clarence pays his bedridden friend a visit at the hospital, but what Clarence thinks will cheer him up might actually drive Belson totally crazy!

added.title: Jeff Wins
added.description: Jeff enlists Clarence to help him prepare for the big Aberdale cook-off. Will Jeff keep his cool or freak out and toss his dish away like in years past?

added.title: Suspended
added.description: Clarence and Sumo hit the jackpot when they get suspended for a week, learning all sorts of different facts they'd never learn in class, but after a few days the suspension takes its toll, boredom sets in and the boys want to go back.

added.title: Transitional Phase
added.description: Life in the RV is interrupted when Uncle Grandpa and the gang keep mysteriously being sent back and forth through time.

added.title: Cartoon Factory
added.description: Uncle Grandpa visits the cartoon factory to get some answers about his roots.

added.title: Date with Gus
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa and Pizza Steve accidentally ruin Mr. Gus' night, the two of them go undercover as Mr. Gus's date.

added.title: What's the Big Idea?
added.description: Pizza Steve and Mr. Gus try to help Uncle Grandpa get an idea.

added.title: Full Grown Pizza
added.description: Uncle Grandpa makes it hard for Pizza Steve to prove he's not a baby.

added.title: The Temple of Madness
added.description: Jay must stand alone against Unagami in the end-game, yet Unagami has a bigger battle in facing the truth about his own identity.

added.title: Game Over
added.description: Unagami breaks into the real world and terrorizes Ninjago City while Jay, Zane and Pixal attempt to prevent disaster by reuniting Unagami with his creator, Milton Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: The ninja are invited to attend the birthday party of Princess Vania, in the distant Kingdom of Shintaro. They depart, bringing along Master Wu, unaware that he is feeling his age…

added.title: Into the Dark
added.description: When Cole investigates a mysterious visitor, the ninja aren't sure what to believe. Cole is frustrated with this lack of team support, until Princess Vania reveals a secret entrance that leads to an underground mine beneath Shintaro - where the city's dark secrets are held.

added.title: The Worst Rescue Ever
added.description: The ninja attempt to rescue Cole, but the bickering of his fellow prisoners, the Geckles and Munce, alerts the Skull Sorcerer, and soon the ninja are prisoners too.

added.title: The Bakugan Battle League Dash/The Final Stage
added.description: The Bakugan Battle League Dash: With Dan and Ajit eliminated from the Bakugan Battle League - Tokyo Edition, the remaining Awesome Brawlers - Shun, Wynton, Lia and Lightning race to complete the second stage of the competition. In order to make it to the final stage, the gang will have to pull together to defeat some tough competition./The Final Stage: It's the final stage of the Bakugan Battle League Tokyo Edition! The remaining Awesome Brawlers are ready to go, but just as the final round begins, the competitors are surprised with some unwelcome guests.

added.title: The Tokyo Catastrophe/Bakugan Battle League Finale
added.description: The Tokyo Catastrophe: Haavik has highjacked the Bakugan Battle league - Tokyo Edition! He's been using the tournament as a platform for his sinister plot to bring chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo./Bakugan Battle League Finale: Haavik unleashes an army of unruly Bakugan to bring his own brand of chaos and destruction to the city of Tokyo. It's all hands-on-deck to stop the invasion, and foil Haavik's plot.

added.title: Champion of the Universe, Dan!/Operation Babysitter
added.description: Champion of the Universe, Dan!: Dan starts "sleep brawling", rolling out Drago causing damage and confusion while he's fast asleep. With the help of a "sleep expert", Ajit attempts to stop Dan and put his "sleep brawling" to rest once and for all./Operation Babysitter: Ajit lands a job babysitting a rambunctious toddler - Aiden. Having no experience with kids, Ajit recruits Wynton to help him out. Things get a little out of hand when Aiden rolls out - Krakelious. Now, Ajit and Wynton have a tiny Baku-brawler on their hands, with no way to stop him!

added.title: Beastie Team Battle/Ajit and Lia
added.description: Beastie Team Battle: China Riot is on the lookout for a partner to team up with in the new Bakugan battle team tournament being held in Los Volmos. Riot may have only been after a brawling partner, but ends up with a new friend./Ajit and Lia: Lia knows the story of where Ajit found his Golden Baku-balls, but no one knows "how" he's able to partner with Golden Bakugan. To get the inside scoop, Lia tags along with Ajit at his new job as a security guard at the local Museum.

added.title: Once More into the Maze/Grandpas in the Wild
added.description: Once More into the Maze: Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett were spotted at the ruins where the great core cell is housed! Alarmed by the report from Benton Dusk, the Awesome Brawlers head to the Yucatan Peninsula to investigate./Grandpas in the Wild: During an all-out brawl with Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, the Awesome Brawlers are hit with an attack that sends everyone spiraling to various parts of the maze. Split up from the rest of the gang, Wynton and Lightning find themselves in a strange unfamiliar part of the maze. While trying to get their bearings, they discover some new golden allies.

added.title: Cabeza de Playa
added.description: Después de viajar a Tampa Beach, Florida, el equipo Tennyson espera poder descansar y relajarse, pero las tempestades sin temperamento, los Climáticos, tienen otros planes que Ben debe frustrar: iconstruir una nueva base en la playa!

added.title: Encantadas
added.description: Durante una comida familiar en un campamento forestal, Charmcaster usa su magia para cambiar de lugar con Gwen, pero cuando Ben descubre a "Charmcaster" husmeando, ataca, sin darse cuenta de que en realidad es su hechizada prima.

added.title: Hotel para perros
added.description: Cuando los Osos no tienen dónde quedarse mientras fumigan su cueva, reservan una noche en un hotel para perros.

added.title: Viaje con Osos
added.description: Para ayudar a recaudar dinero para salvar la tienda de Darrell, los Osos usan el tronco como taxi a través de una aplicación de viajes compartidos.

added.title: El Show de Nom Nom
added.description: Las cosas se complican cuando Nom Nom filma su primer programa de televisión. Los Osos se ofrecen a ayudar y aparecen en el programa.

added.title: Cueva Helada
added.description: Ralph se apodera de la cueva y la convierte en una fortaleza nevada, donde reina sobre los Osos y Charlie.

added.title: Dia de Spa
added.description: Los Osos se relajan en el spa. Grizz intenta usar todos los servicios del spa. Panda queda atrapado en la sala de vapor con un anciano. Y Polar juega al ping pong.

added.title: Big Ben 10
added.description: Cuando Ben y su familia viajan a Londres para visitar el legendario Big Ben, los hermanos Bicho están allí para darles la bienvenida, obviamente con un nuevo plan escandalosamente exagerado: iencoger la campana del Big Ben para robarla!

added.title: Cyber Luchadores
added.description: En Biggie Box Japón, Ben espera en una fila épica el lanzamiento de Cyber Luchadores, el último videojuego de Luchadores de Sumo. Pero muy pronto, Ben debe salvar la tienda: no de los clientes ansiosos por comprar el juego sino de Vapor Smythe, ique quiere modernizar un mecanismo gigantesco con sus vandálicos poderes de vapor!

added.title: La Grange Muralla
added.description: Ben, Gwen y el abuelo Max hacen un viaje a la Gran Muralla, pero su aventura por poco termina arruinada por los temerarios LaGrange y Vin Etanol, que intentan saltar sobre el monumento internacional. Ben debe subirse al Rustbuggy para ahuyentar a los enemigos.

added.title: El Templo de la Locura
added.description: Jay debe enfrentarse solo a Unagami en el juego final, pero Unagami tiene una batalla más grande al enfrentarse a la verdad sobre su propia identidad.

added.title: Juego Terminado
added.description: Unagami entra al mundo real y aterroriza a la ciudad de Ninjago mientras Jay, Zane y Pixal intentan evitar el desastre reuniendo a Unagami con Dyer.

added.title: Shintaro
added.description: Los Ninjas están invitados a asistir a la fiesta de cumpleaños de la princesa Vania en la ciudad de Shintaro. Llevan al Maestro Wu que está deprimido.

added.title: En la Oscuridad
added.description: La princesa Vania revela una entrada secreta que conduce a una mina subterránea bajo Shintaro donde se guardan los oscuros secretos de la ciudad.

added.title: El Peor Rescate de la Historia
added.description: Los Ninjas intentan rescatar a Cole, pero las discusiones entre prisioneros alertan al Hechicero Calavera, y hace prisioneros a los otros Ninjas.

added.title: Dia de profesionales
added.description: Después de un gasto excesivo, Golden Goose le dice a la pandilla que no les dará más huevos de oro hasta que aprendan el valor del dinero. Siguiendo el consejo de Rick de ahorrar dinero, la pandilla abrió una tienda de galletas para ganar dinero por su cuenta y guardarla en una gran bóveda.

added.title: Asteroide Triste
added.description: Un asteroide viaja directo hacia el reino, por lo que la Dra. Fox se pone al frente de la banda en una misión para volar en un cohete hasta la superficie del asteroide y hacerlo explotar en pedazos con una enorme bomba para así salvar el reino. Pero al llegar, la banda descubre que el asteroide solitario es en realidad un tipo sumamente agradable y se rehúsan a hacerlo explotar. Por desgracia, el asteroide se entera del plan de Fox y sale corriendo llorando, icon la bomba aún en su interior! La Dra. Fox, arrepentida, lleva de urgencia a la banda tras el asteroide para levantarle el ánimo antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: El gran viaje
added.description: Es hora de las vacaciones anuales de la banda, pero Halcondrilo se niega a ir, alegando que las vacaciones de la banda nunca son divertidas para él porque los otros son pésimos compañeros de vacaciones. De hecho, Halcondrilo solo acepta ir si la banda aprueba su curso de entrenamiento de vacaciones superintensivo: ilos desafíos temáticos más emocionantes que se puedan imaginar!

added.title: Charlas Nocturnas
added.description: La luna está aburrida de tomar el turno de noche, ya que todos siempre están dormidos. Entonces, Unikitty lidera a la pandilla en la presentación de un programa de entrevistas nocturno exagerado para mantener la luna ocupada.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Unireino
added.description: Después de descubrir que el turismo escasea en el Unireino, Unikitty recluta a la banda para que hagan un video que inspire a la gente a visitar el reino. Pero luego de varias calamidades, Unikitty comienza a creer que el video resultará siendo un desastre. Sin embargo, los amigos salvan el día con algo de creatividad y logran hacer que un solo turista los visite. iMisión cumplida!

added.title: El chico del 3030
added.description: Los niños conocen a un misterioso niño del futuro y tratan de ayudarlo a completar su misión.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Punos Fuertes
added.description: Harto de perder cuando juega a los videojuegos contra su padre, Craig busca entrenarse en el Arroyo.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Carrera en el Arroyo
added.description: Una carrera de alta velocidad con un premio de alto riesgo puede ser demasiado para Craig y sus amigos.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Club de Lectura Secreto
added.description: Kelsey crea un club de lectura supersecreto para introducir a Craig y JP en las alegrías de la lectura.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Princesa gotica
added.description: Gwen lleva por accidente un pony de peluche rosado que le encanta a la guardería, y pasa todo el día negando que es suyo.

added.title: Jextra Perrestre
added.description: JP cree que puede ser de otro planeta, así que Craig trata de ayudarlo a hacer contacto.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Goma pegajosa
added.description: A Beth se le atasca la goma de mascar en el cabello de Leshawna y tiene que sacarla- sin que Leshawna descubra que está ahí.

added.title: Invasion de los mocos ladrones
added.description: Harold cree que el fotógrafo del día de la foto oficial está convirtiendo a los niños en zombies que se portan bien.

added.title: Mentiras lastimosas
added.description: Beth y Leshawna tratan de superarse uno a la otra con heridas falsas mientras compiten por la atención y comprensión de los otros niños en la guardería.

added.title: Derretidor
added.description: Cuando Chef le dice a Beth que no comprará el nuevo juguete súper increíble que ella quiere porque ya tienen mucho con qué jugar, ella emprende una misión para librarse de sus juguetes.

added.title: Davey
added.description: Finn can't go anywhere without folks stopping to thank him for being a hero.

added.title: Fallen Arches/The Mane Event
added.description: Fallen Arches: When a gang of old-time villains come out of retirement, the girls enlist the best superhero team of the past to save the city./The Mane Event: Bubbles and Buttercup are playing with Blossom's beautiful locks when an accident happens. Now, Blossom is too embarrassed to put up a good fight.

added.title: Cave Sweet Cave
added.description: After the Joker floods the Batcave, the Batwheels evacuate and relocate to a nearby parking garage. As they adapt to their temporary home, they learn important lessons about family and making the most of what you have.

added.title: Scaredy-Bat
added.description: When Batman refuses to engage Joker in a race, Prank goads Bam into a rematch. Can Bam learn to not give in to the bully's dares and take the high road?

added.title: Rock On
added.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Mac and Tosh Gopher to build them a home underground. Daffy can't remove rocks from the area fast enough and fails to ask for help.

added.title: Buzz In
added.description: Bizzy Buzzard's mom hires The Looney Builders to build her family a new nest. Bizzy wants to help but keeps getting in the way creating all sorts of problems for the crew.

added.title: That's the Way the Windmill Blows!/Mecha Machine Makers!
added.description: The windmill isn't turning, which means Sunny Field Farm has no power. The windmill needs to turn again so Zee can launch his rocket!/Izzy and Timmy are making a bird caller for Grandma, but have trouble connecting pieces of their machine.

added.title: The Need for Feed/The Zipline Sisters of Treetop Woods
added.description: MacBarm is bringing food to his hungry chickens, that is, until all of the food falls out of his truck./Grandma and her twin sister want to recreate their old zipline act, but quickly discover that the zipline no longer exists!

added.title: The Real Number One
added.description: When Thomas' #1 is covered by paint, he sets out to prove to himself that he is still number one, but when everything starts to go wrong for him, he learns what it really means to be #1.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Roller Coasting
added.description: Thomas wants to show Percy what it's like to ride a roller coaster, so Thomas turns the tracks of Sodor into a thrill ride.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: No Power, No Problem!
added.description: When the power goes out all over Sodor, Thomas and Friends must use brain-power to navigate the island in creative new ways.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: The Tiger Train
added.description: When Yong Bao visits Sodor, a jealous Thomas sets out to prove he's the braver train and challenges Yong Bao to a series of bravery challenges, only to have his plan backfire.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Can-Do Submarine Crew
added.description: Thomas and Percy think they're great communicators, but when they're tasked with delivering a submarine to Vicarstown, communication becomes a bit more difficult… to say the least!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Ducks
added.description: Blippi gets up close and personal with Declan the Duck in his quest to find how ducks float! Under the water, above the water, through feather tunnels and tooting air bubbles, Blippi and Declan work together to discover the answer.

added.title: Birds Nest
added.description: A storm has destroyed Jodie the Blue Jays bird nest! Good thing Blippi and FETCH are there to help. While FETCH is on egg-sitting duty, Jodie and Blippi go on a heist mission to acquire the materials needed to rebuild. It's never an impossible mission when friends work together!

added.title: Bats
added.description: Can you see in the dark? Blippi can't either! But on this adventure Blippi and FETCH fly around in the dark with Matt the Bat who shows them how he uses echolocation to see and hear in the dark! Who needs eyes when you can use echo-echo-echoes?

added.title: Crane
added.description: It's the first day on the job for Kareem the Crane, and he's feeling very nervous. Luckily, Blippi and FETCH are there to lend a helping hand! Working together they help Kareem to do his work. Kareem gains confidence and Blippi learns how cranes help to build a skyscraper!

added.title: Flies
added.description: Lunch is ready! Prepared to eat his delicious sandwich, Blippi notices his old friend Horace the Fly. Horace is walking upside down on the ceiling, and after shrinking down, Blippi joins him. But how does Horace stick to the ceiling? A musical song and dance from Horace is the best way to find out!

added.title: Old Macdonald
added.description: Rishi goes around the farm with Ella, organising all the animals so they can have a soccer game!

added.title: Shake the Apple Tree
added.description: It's the end of the summer and the trees are full of delicious apples ready to be picked!

added.title: O'Little Tree
added.description: Mei shows Ella and Rishi the magic of Christmas - by growing an adorable Christmas tree in the middle of the farm.

added.title: Mr. McStuffles
added.description: Daffy doesn't want to give up his old toy, even after he's outgrown it.

added.title: Picture This!
added.description: The babies create their own endings to fairytales.

added.title: Hair Cut-Ups
added.description: Lola is afraid of getting her first haircut.

added.title: A Clean Sweep
added.description: Daffy tries to avoid cleaning up by sweeping his toys under a rug.

added.title: Daffy Did It!
added.description: Tweety blames Daffy for his mistake, and then has trouble living with the guilt of lying.

removed.title: Separacion Rapida
removed.description: Cuando una misteriosa tormenta eléctrica se abate sobre el Omni-Copter en el Ecuador, el equipo Tennyson pronto descubre que Solar y Polar están detrás del suceso.

removed.title: Las Dos Espadas
removed.description: Para escapar de la prisión del Hechicero Calavera, los Ninjas debe convencer a los Munces y a Geckles de que dejen de discutir y trabajen juntos.

removed.title: El Bentatlon
removed.description: El equipo Tennyson se dirige a la verdadera Grecia en el Omni-Copter. Pero cuando de repente son capturados por el Caballero por Siempre a mitad de vuelo, Ben termina en un coliseo, donde se enfrenta a algunos viejos enemigos.

removed.title: El Hechicero Calavera
removed.description: Separado de los demás, Cole debe encontrar su camino a la superficie para advertir al Rey Vangelis sobre el peligroso Hechicero Calavera.

removed.title: El precio de un consejo
removed.description: Cuando una esfera de la fortuna de origami le dice a Izzy que es la mejor consejera de vida del mundo, está decidida a probar que es así.

removed.title: La madre de todas las tarjetas
removed.description: Chef intenta engañar a los niños para que hagan su regalo del Día de la Madre después que él olvida la festividad.

removed.title: La Reina de los Munces
removed.description: Jay, Nya y Lloyd son guiados entre las minas de Shintaro por Murt, quien los lleva de vuelta a la Cueva de los Munces. A la Reina Munce le gusta Jay.

removed.title: Las Garras del Gato
removed.description: Mientras disfruta de las vistas y los sonidos de un festival de música, Ben se eriza ante la sugerencia de Gwen de ser su nueva compañera, ya que el festival está amenazado por las ondas sonoras supersónicas de Lord Decibel.

removed.title: Juicio de Mino
removed.description: Un grupo de Geckles creen que Kai y Zane están aliados con el Hechicero Calavera y los llevan con su líder, quien los somete a un juicio por Mino…

removed.title: Cirque-Ados
removed.description: Ben es el invitado de honor de una gala, pero cuando el espectáculo del circo resulta ser Zombozo disfrazado, Ben no solo debe derrotar al malvado payaso, sino también a su misterioso nuevo compañero, iPirueta!

removed.title: Demasiada baba
removed.description: Beth se niega a creer que la adorable criatura de baba que ha creado con limo esté comiéndose a los niños hasta que ella y Gwen son las únicas dos que quedan en la clase.

removed.title: Carretera por Siempre
removed.description: Durante una carrera de aceleración, Ben espera mantenerse al mismo nivel con Vin Etanol y La Grange como XLR8. Pero cuando su reloj hace cortocircuito una y otra vez, nuestro héroe debe ser creativo si quiere seguir el ritmo de sus rápidos y furiosos enemigos.

removed.title: La Gran Caida
removed.description: Este episodio relata cómo Cole, la princesa Vania y el maestro Wu caen por un túnel aparentemente interminable, dentro de la montaña de Shintaro.

removed.title: Conejo culpable
removed.description: Chef intenta conservar su cordura cuando los niños culpan repetidamente a un conejo de peluche llamado Saltarín de todo lo que ellos han hecho.

removed.title: Duncan liberado
removed.description: Duncan se escapa durante un paseo en la comunidad solo para descubrir que tiene que cuidar a Cody y Bridgette.

removed.title: The Color of Monkey
removed.description: Everybody's favorite alien conman, Argit, takes on a shady sidekick, Simian, in a shocking new business.

removed.title: Vreedlemania
removed.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

removed.title: Ken 10
removed.description: We're back in the future with Ben 10K, and this time he has a son, Ken. On Ken's tenth birthday, Ben gives him his very own Omnitrix. Ben must come to learn to trust Ken with the power of the Omnitrix. Along the way, Ken befriends a kid named Devlin. Devlin turns out to be Kevin 11's son and was merely using Ken so he could break his dad out of the Null Void. Ben 10K and Ken then team up to take down Kevin 11. As for Devlin, he comes to realize his dad is a jerk, and realizes the error of his ways. He's able to redeem himself, proving he's a good kid and joining forces with "Team Tennyson."

removed.title: Ben 4 Good Buddy
removed.description: Out on a desert highway, a group of modern day highway pirates hijack the Rustbucket, trick it out and use it in a daring robbery. And while Ben and Gwen are at first glad to get rid of that "bucket of bolts", they come to realize the Rustbucket is "a part of the family." In the end our trio heroes get Max's beloved "ride" back and bring down these pirates once and for all.

removed.title: Ready to Rumble
removed.description: After Ben thinks he's broken Gwen's computer, he sneaks off and enters an "ultimate wrestling competition" to win enough money to buy her a new one. On the mat as Fourarms, he becomes an instant celebrity hit with the fans and ends up going up against a tandem of odd looking brothers with special mutant-like powers. Initially adversaries, Ben and the brothers become allies when Ben discovers the brothers are beholden to a powerful mob boss. Ben helps the brothers defeat the mob boss and his henchmen, and in the end realizes Gwen's computer was never really broken.

removed.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 1
removed.description: Alternate dimensions, duplicate Bens and villains from throughout time and space! Just another day in Bellwood.

removed.title: It's a Mad, Mad, Mad Ben World Part 2
removed.description: Ben and Dr. Psychobos become reluctant allies in a parallel-dimension maelstrom.

removed.title: Big Fat Alien Wedding
removed.description: Ben and Gwen accompany Max to a wedding, which doesn't make Ben particularly happy, especially given the fact he has to wear a tux and learn how to dance. During the wedding it's revealed that the bride's parents are aliens while the groom's family are ex-Plumbers. It turns out the bride's parents are out to sabotage the wedding because of a long lasting feud with the Plumbers, and take action by demonstrating their destructive powers and causing deadly havoc. Ben, Max and Gwen enter the fray and not only save the day, but make sure the ceremony goes on as planned.

removed.title: Breakpoint
removed.description: As Wildvine, Ben goes undercover with an alien crime ring and is tempted by their extreme lifestyle.

removed.title: The Super-Long Shortcut
removed.description: When Gordon is unable to make an important delivery on his own, Thomas offers his help, but Gordon insists on second-guessing Thomas's every move.

removed.title: Get Active Dance
removed.description: Mei, Ella, animals and vegetables have a farm active day exercising and organising the farm

removed.title: Ocean
removed.description: Blippi's trusty BlippiMobile safely transports him to a whole new underwater world! He dives into the sea, where he gets an ocean tour from a local resident, Jerry the Jellyfish. They swim through a huge kelp forest, explore the ocean floor and meet interesting underwater creatures along the way!

removed.title: Happy Place
removed.description: Time to share some of the honey made at Lellobee City Farm with everyone that visits the farm

removed.title: Cheesy Peasy
removed.description: The Looney Builders are hired by the Mouse Sisters to build a bridge over a mac and cheese spill. Lola turns the job into a game which results in the crew losing sight of the bigger goal.

removed.title: Blippi Learns Rainbow Colors
removed.description: Have you ever wondered how a rainbow gets its colors? Join Blippi and his sidekick TABBS on their first adventure as they discover the science behind rainbows!

removed.title: Gravity
removed.description: Three, two, one, lift-off! On this mission to the moon, Blippi bounces around with Rocky the Moon Rock. Light as a feather they bound up and float back down, teaching Blippi all about gravity! One small step for Blippi, one giant leap for Blippi.

removed.title: Salad Salsa
removed.description: Mei, Ella, animals cook a delicious salad using local vegetables

removed.title: Eggsellent Adventure
removed.description: Thomas and Percy have a difficult delivery - getting eggs and other cake ingredients safely to Vicarstown for their bake-off.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Tyrannosaurus Wrecks
removed.description: Thomas and the other Engines get to deliver some newly discovered dinosaur bones, but they must deliver them in the correct order for assembly, which isn't as easy as it sounds...
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Calliope Crack-Up
removed.description: When the engines are delivering attractions to the annual Harwick Beach Carnival, a series of mistakes causes the precious Calliope to break. Luckily, the engines come up with a creative solution.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: Honey
removed.description: Blippi and FETCH shrink down and fly inside a very active beehive, where they meet Bijon, the fast-talking, fast-moving Worker Bee. With a talent for rhyming and making honey, Bijon rhymes her way through the sweet explanation of how delicious honey is made. What a very buzzy... erm...busy day!

removed.title: Riddle Me This
removed.description: After struggling to solve a riddle from Riddler's helicopter Quizz, Redbird must learn to speak up and share his ideas with the Batwheels if they hope to figure out the villain's true scheme.

removed.title: Zoomsday
removed.description: The Legion of Zoom is tired of always losing. They decide to take a page from the Batwheels and try using teamwork in order to pull off a daring heist. But will they be able to work together?

removed.title: Stories
removed.description: The Looney Builders are hired by Hoots Talon to expand and paint the old library. They enlist master painter Sylvester who faces his fear of heights with his build buddy, Tweety.

removed.title: Let's Get Rolling!/A Bit of a Stretch!
removed.description: It's MacBarm's croquet tournament and Zee made giant decorations but they're too big to get to the farm./It's the opening day of the skyscraper and the Mechas need to put the sphere on top of the building before the ribbon cutting ceremony.

removed.title: Popsicle
removed.description: Blippi shrinks down and goes on a sweet and exciting adventure through an ice cream truck with Sherry Pop, a fruit popsicle, finding out that she and all frozen treats need to be in the ice-cold so they won't melt.

removed.title: A Light Delivery
removed.description: When Thomas accidentally breaks a light he's hauling to the Sodor Festival of Lights, he learns the best way to be the #1 engine is to be honest when you make a mistake.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: The Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods/Nat in the Dark!
removed.description: Berta is opening an exhibit on the Whatsacallit of Treetop Woods. If only she could get a picture to prove it's real./Gerry and Nat are leading the Treetop Troops on a hike, but Nat finds himself lost in the woods as it gets darker.

removed.title: Forever Road
removed.description: During a drag race, Ben hopes to stay neck and neck with Vin Ethanol and La Grange as XLR8, but when his watch keeps shorting out, our hero must get creative if he is to keep up with his fast and furious foes!

removed.title: Cirque-Us
removed.description: After saving a State University Alumni ribbon cutting ceremony, Ben becomes the guest of honor at the upcoming Gala, but when the cirque entertainment turns out be Zombozo, in disguise, Ben must not only defeat the evil clown but his mysterious new sidekick, Pirouette!

removed.title: The Claws of the Cat
removed.description: While taking in the sights and sounds of a Rio de Jenaro music festival, Ben bristles at Gwen's suggestion that she be his new sidekick, but when the festival is threaten by the supersonic sound waves of Lord Decibel, our hero must lean on help from some familiar faces: DJ Gpa and Gwen-Cat!

removed.title: The Bentathlon
removed.description: After stuffing their faces with gyros, Team Tennyson makes their way to the real Greece in the Omni-Copter, but when they are suddenly captured by the Forever Knight mid-flight, Ben ends up in a coliseum, where he is pit against old foes: Iron Kyle, Queen Bee, and the Ground Hawgs!

removed.title: Lickety Split
removed.description: When a mysterious electrical storm downs the Omni-Copter at the Equator, Team Tennyson soon discovers Solar & Polar are behind it, but when Ben accidentally combines the two into a more powerful Uni-Twin, our hero must think fast if he is going to save the planet!

removed.title: The Price of Advice
removed.description: After a paper origami fortune teller tells Izzy she's the world's best advice giver, she's determined to prove it.

removed.title: Too Much of a Goo'd Thing
removed.description: Beth refuses to believe that the adorable goo creature she's created out of slime is consuming the kids until she and Gwen are the only two left in class.

removed.title: There Are No Hoppy Endings
removed.description: Chef struggles to maintain his sanity when the kids continue to blame a stuffed rabbit named Hoppy for everything they do wrong.

removed.title: Duncan Disorderly
removed.description: Duncan escapes during a community walk only to discover he has to babysit Cody and Bridgette.

removed.title: Mother of All Cards
removed.description: Chef attempts to trick the kids into making his mother gifts after he forgets Mother's Day.

removed.title: Who's the Fake?!/Trouble Busters! 2
removed.description: With the reveal that Haavik is a shapeshifting Alien, the ABs start to get super-paranoid, realizing that ANYONE could be Haavik in disguise. The suspicion quickly turns inward, and the ABs are left wondering if they have an imposter among them!/ A kid brawler named Oliver has lost his Bakugan! This seems like a job for the Trouble Busters. The Awesome Brawlers help him chase down and try to catch the elusive Bakugan, who leads them on a wild goose chase through Los Volmos.

removed.title: The Past Revealed/Run! A Storm's on the Way
removed.description: The Past Revealed: After getting lost in maze with Lia, Ajit remembers the day he met Pharol and Auxilataur. He finally can explain how he was able to partner with golden Bakugan, but Ajit's story is interrupted by a familiar face - Storm!/Run! A Storm's on the Way: Still upset that Ajit has given up his life as a phantom thief, Storm rolls out Hydranoid x Aquos and attacks! Ajit and Lia take off running through the maze as Storm gives chase.

removed.title: Dusk Industries Under Attack/Taking Dan Back
removed.description: Dusk Industries Under Attack: "Bad Dan" has his taken his rampage to Dusk Industries and this time he has help spreading the chaos and destruction, he's joined by Sophie, McQ, Everett, Storm and Haavik! The Awesome Brawlers are quickly on the scene try to bring an end to the show of destruction./ Taking Dan Back: "Bad Dan" with Haavik's crew and their fusion Bakugan continue the rampage at Dusk Industries. The Awesome Brawlers, with some help from Magnus, are determined to an end to this show of destruction and get their friend back!

removed.title: Golden Bakugan Encounter/Ties of Gold
removed.description: Golden Bakugan Encounter: Dan and Shun, split up from the rest of Awesome Brawlers, are traveling in through the maze when they discover McQ. It turns out McQ is seeking a golden Bakugan. When the boys go in for a closer look, they are startled by an old friend, and together confront McQ./Ties of Gold: The now reunited Awesome Brawlers are once again confronted by Storm, McQ, Sophie and Everett, who are on the hunt for golden Bakugan. With tired Bakugan, the Awesome Brawlers will have to give it their all to defend against this evil.

removed.title: Nightmare/Bad Dan
removed.description: Nightmare: Dan hasn't been sleeping well lately. No "sleep brawling" this time, but he's constantly tossing and turning.
